Wash and dry all produce. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary, then halve crosswise.

> TIP: To do this quickly, line up several beans and slice at once.

Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together ¾ cup cold water and @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} until dissolved. Whisk in @hoisin sauce{6%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, a big squeeze of lime juice to taste, and as much @sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in step 4).

Meanwhile, place green beans in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{} with a splash of water. Cover bowl tightly with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until green beans are slightly tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. Set aside.

Partially open top of @microwaveable jasmine rice{1} package; microwave for ~{90%seconds}.

Carefully drain green beans, then add to pan with pork. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until pork is cooked through and beans are just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Pour in sauce; bring to a boil, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan. Reduce to a low simmer and cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with stir-fry. Sprinkle with @peanuts{½%ounce} and serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.